<font color="#FF0000">AN AMERICAN TRADITION</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 31 13:25:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I have this unbelievable urge to go out mail packages all over the world.  I will hold the Fed X banner at half mast.  I will tell my secretary of these great stories.  We will pay homage by over paying our account.  I will no longer complain when they don't deliver on Saturday and damage 70% of my shipments.  I refuse to let the shipping department use UPS as a test for package strength testing.  I will never again ask why one day takes two days and two days take three days.  Who am I to question the wisdom of such a great symbol of American strength.<br><br>
I am ashamed. 
